 And janny in her 'kerchief, and I in my cap,
 Had just settled our bans for a long winter's nap,
 When out in a thread there arose such a clatter,
 I sprang from my bed to see what was the matter.
 And off to the front page I flew right away,
 Clicked open the sticky to see what was at play.
 The style of special on the posts I beheld,
 Gave a hint of magic to the words that were spelled,
 When what to my wondering eyes did out poke,
 But a reposted meme of eight heckin' trans folk,
 From a rascally anon so well dressed and fly,

 On, Lily! on, Liam! on, Chloe and Brayden!
 To the top of the page! to the top of the board!
 Now bump away! bump away! we won't be ignored!"

the other issue is that trans healthcare is unlike almost any other field because it's, in my opinion, the only kind of medicine that is not just medical but cosmetic. part of the reason DIY is (when done ideally) more effective than what you'd get with almost any doctor is because the goals are fundamentally different: you are trying to not just change your biology but aesthetically improve yourself, while from the doctor's perspective it doesn't matter at all if you have no aesthetic change whatsoever; they just want you to not die/get physically sick (either by suicide or overdosing or underdosing hormones or something). this is on top of most of their knowledge being woefully outdated, and not bothering to keep up-to-date, and typically not being trained on or specialized in trans matters in general. it's a complete mismatch

the theoretical best practitioners/"hormone therapists" for this specialized, narrow field would almost exclusively be self-taught amateurs - probably some people off of 4chan and reddit, honestly - but of course they don't have a medical license so there's no way to legally do this. and then there are probably like 5 doctors in the world who do the kind of thing these self-taught amateurs would do in addition to having a medical license, like Powers, but of course they can't serve everyone, and the kinds of doctors to do that are generally probably weird in other ways (like Powers)

>QOTT2: Have any holiday recipes to share with the rest of us? Be it food, drink or anything in between.
Well I'm glad you asked OP
Let me repost the recipe from last thread, since I need to make a few corrections

12 egg yolks
1 cup of sugar
2 cups heavy cream
4 cups whole milk
About a teaspoon nutmeg
A pinch of salt
teaspoon vanilla
teaspoon of cinnamon

Blend the egg yolks and sugar together until smooth and creamy
Heat the cream and milk over medium heat until it gets nearly scalding
Temper the eggs with the cream and milk mixture, then put it back onto the heat
Stir continuously until the mixture is thick enough to coat the back of a wooden spoon
(if you are concerned about raw/undercooked eggs, you can use a thermometer and make sure it reaches 160F/70C)
Add the spices and vanilla, then refrigerate

And I didn't get to post it cuz of the character limit:

The other recipe I've got on hand is for shortbread cookies, which are generally very simple recipes. This one is intended to be used for jam sandwich cookies, picrel is last year's batch

For the cookies:
3/4 cups of butter, warmed to room temperature
1/2 teaspoon of salt
2 3/4 cups of all purpose flour
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
1/2 cups sugar

Blend the butter until it's fluffy, then blend in sugar and salt
Next, blend the egg and vanilla
Then finally the flour.
Knead the dough into a smooth ball, and divide into equal halves
Roll it out and press it into shapes

For picrel, I used a couple drinking glasses, one large and one small, to make the bottom and top halves.

For the filling: any fruit preserve or jam you like!
For the garnish: a dusting of powdered sugar will do

I'll actually be making these cookies later today, so I can report back and reassure everyone that they're still as tasty as I remember.

This barely counts as a recipe but
>Anon’s Caffeinated Cocoa
———
>You will need:
>Two 12oz coffee cups
>Coffee grinder with a “coarse” setting (for best results, use a conical burr grinder)
>34oz French Press coffee maker (I use a bodum)
>Pot and heater
>1/2 cup of fresh whole bean espresso (for best results, use coffee roasted between 5-10 days ago, get a blend without lots of acidity/fruity tasting notes, and don’t buy from a chain)
>Two splashes of half&half
>Two packets of hot cocoa from pic related
———
Brewing tasty coffee is very similar to mixing a great cocktail. Your primary ingredient is doing most of the work, so shop around a little and find a blend of espresso you really like. If you don’t feel like climbing down the specialty coffee rabbit hole, I used Ritual Coffee’s “Sweater Weather” seasonal espresso.

Bring a pot of water to a boil.
Once at a full boil, take it off the heat and quickly set a kitchen timer for 60 seconds. Pour your 1/2 cup of coffee beans into your grinder, grind ‘em up, and dump the grounds in your French Press. When the timer is up, slowly pour in the water - pouring in a circular or zig-zag motion if you want to get fancy with it. Stop when there’s about 1 inch of space left between the top of the French Press and the frothy beanwater slurry. Quickly start another kitchen timer for 4:00. Leave the lid off the French Press.

While the coffee is brewing, get out your cups and hot cocoa packets. Pour one packet in each cup. When the timer goes off, put the lid on the French Press and slowly (but firmly) depress the plunger. Maybe ask if it’s spending another Christmas alone, idk. Fill each cup almost all the way to the top, then stir until there aren’t any clumps of dry cocoa on the bottom of the cup. Add a splash of half & half to finish. You might have to add some, stir it in, sip your coffee to check if it’s enough, then add a little more to taste.

You’re done! Enjoy!

If you forced yourself back into a relationship, even if by proximity alone you somehow regained feelings or formed new feelings for him, the nagging doubt about the situation would remain. The issue is, if the guy is genuine about his regret, I personally would say he deserves a chance to prove himself to you. It's your call whether you think he deserves it, I can only base this off of my perspective and say I wouldn't distance myself. The point is that the reason you would not trust your own feelings if you tried to get back together is because he's placed that seed of unreliability in your mind, but if he somehow shows to you that you can trust him again then that changes the situation. This involves a lot of interpretation of his conviction and whether you can still see your lives intertwining forwards into the future, so like I said it's ultimately your call. There will be no easy decision to make in this situation, that's why betrayal from those you love hurts so much, but in the absence of a decision that you'll be fully satisfied with, you have to make the decision that you think will lead to either your own development as a person or the mutual development of the both of you if you still desire that.

>Why is this thread /lgbt/?
Struggles with mental and physical health are an indisputable part of /lgbt/ life, be it from dysphoria, social pressure, heartbreak, or just unfortunate lifestyle choices.
>Notes to consider:
Please be civil. Shame is your greatest enemy in fighting urges of self abuse (be it sh, drugs, or just self deprecation). WE ARE NOT THERAPISTS, WE DON'T REPLACE MEDICATION

may as well try to be helpful:

for anyone else trapped in dissocation, especially depersonalization and derealization, it was the bodily awareness, trying to locate my body in space that knocked me out of it. not just trying to say where they are, but to be aware of where my entire body is simultaniously. basically allowing myself to accept the signals from my body and "listening". it's hard to explain. physical therapy tried to teach me to improve my propioception and this kind of grew out of that.

after that, the derealization part of it fades in and out a bit, but what helped me with that was flashing lights on and off on opposite sides of a room (i used an app with smartbulbs to do it) to make me aware of the space around me, as well as listening to 8D music on youtube and trying to imagine where it's coming from, both at the same time. the dual flashing light idea came from me snapping out of it a little when id see flickering lights outside.

hope this helps someone break out of it. don't expect it to work instantly, it took a while for it to start happening. goes double if you're still unhappy with your body.

You know you're brainwormed, which is a good thing. Being in a good, mentally stable place before transitioning may be a sensible choice to make sure you don't immediately cave and detrans. These feelings of inadequacy will consume you if you let them, and weeding them out takes time and effort. Hard to overcome, but given some support and some personal progress you can overcome it. You can change your opinions of yourself. You can change plenty of your wants.
Tranners would however urge you to rather start sooner than later, because it improves your chances, and because there is a chance you will never feel ready. Never, ever set out to a loosely defined goal with ill defined preconditions like that. You will never feel ready then, and just append new arbitrary conditions when you will start for real. Set a clear, realistic, measurable goal. "When my BMI is 23 I will transition", for example. Stick to it, you will never feel adequate or prepared.

Do you feel disgusted by being a man? Would you pick to wake up as a cis woman tomorrow with no hesitation? If you were alone for life on a desert island and had male and female clothes and a lifetime supply of HRT sitting there, what would you do? Would you feel upset if a personality test guessed you're male? If there was a test to see for sure if you have gender dysphoria or not, what result would you hope for? Would you rather be the hottest hunk of a man to ever live or an average woman? Would you transition if everyone in society was totally fine with it? How about if you knew for sure you'd pass? Try sitting down and getting calm and kind of meditative and tell yourself repeatedly, "I am a man." How does that make you feel? How about the same thing with "I am a woman."? If you try it with, "I am going to stay a man for the rest of my life, I will never transition and I will die as a man," how does that feel? What about, "that's it, I'm done fighting feeling this way, I'm going to start transitioning as soon as possible," how does that make you feel?

Just a few exercises to kind of see. It's not definitive or anything but it might help.

They have even been reported as having "voluptuous breasts" (Roy Hertz et al., 1966; Valentine, 1969; Polani, 1970). John McLean Morris, the gynecologist who reviewed and summarized all of the existing scientific literature on CAIS women in 1953 (including 82 cases) and gave their condition the (now-obsolete) name "testicular feminization", described their breasts as "unusually large" and "jumbo-sized" (Morris, 1953; Quigley et al., 1995). He additionally said in his famous 1953 review that they had "normal female breasts, often with a tendency to be overdeveloped" (Morris, 1953). In actuality however, some CAIS women have large breasts while some have small breasts (Wisniewski et al., 2000), and we have no clear data that their breasts are in fact larger on average. The variation in breast growth in CAIS women parallels the same large variation in breast size between individuals that's seen in women in general.

Maybe, but it's a gamble. Some people regain all their hair, some regain none. If it's been ten years, though, I think you may be out of luck. I don't think it's common to regain more than a year or two worth of hair loss. HRT may not stop your hair loss at all, just look at the boomer trannies and IT'S MA'AMs who started late in life and probably had pretty high test before, the damage is already done. FtMs who detransition naturally produce E and they don't regain their lost hair either. Definitely a case of you want to start as early as possible.

If hair is all you care about though, you don't need E, and it probably shouldn't be anywhere near the top of the list of options. E inhibits hair loss as a side effect, the actual thing that stops hair loss is low testosterone. Higher E levels will dampen your T, that's how monotherapy works, but E will have other effects, including breasts, which is going to be a problem if you want to present as conventionally masculine. it's all conjecture, nobody knows. Cis puberty happens by itself so the specifics aren't important, and nobody cares about trannies enough to do much good conclusive research on the best methods for hrt.
The reason estrone is talked about for breast growth, is because there's some evidence (not hard proof) that oral E is better for early breast growth, and oral gives higher estrone. I think there are also cases where hondosed mtfs get really big breasts on low doses of oral E, but little progress in anything else.
A lot of this comes from dr. powers, who is an advocate for the idea that estrone is important for early breast growth, and that estrone should be the dominant hormone until tanner 3.
But as you can see from that study, there isn't a lot of actual evidence to support it.
I think the best way to go about it is probably just to transition normally as well as you can, and then after a year or two when you're on monotherapy, if your breast growth isn't satisfactory you can always add 1mg oral E or something, which apparently has been effective in other people. posts.name: Anonymous
posts.com:
>>28897557
Look at the picture in OP. Also check out https://transfemscience.org/articles/transfem-intro/

The basics is, if you take any estrogen at all, you are going to develop breasts, which doesn't sound like something you're interested in. Heightened levels of estrogen will furthermore suppress your testosterone production, to the extent that a large dose (called estradiol monotherapy) can essentially block it entirely.
You can try taking only an antiandrogen (cypro will probably be the easiest and best option). You won't "feminise", but you will "de-masculinise". It'll kill your libido (it's literally chemical castration) and make erections very rare, but that's reversible if you just stop taking the medication. Over prolonged time it's going to cause brittle bones and other health issues associated with menopause, so bear that in mind and live healthy. Don't try to do this with bica, that one doesn't actually stop test production, just your body's ability to make use of it. All the leftover testosterone turns into estrogen and you'll grow tits.
Testosterone is the stuff that builds muscles, so without it you're going to build muscle at more or less the same rate a woman does, which is significantly slower, but you do keep any muscle you already have, and also your masculine bone structure. Even if you go full MtF HRT you'll be stronger than just about any natural female. If you keep up your exercise you won't lose muscle, but you may lose your appetite (or gain a lot of it), and you will find it difficult to build new muscle.

Needless to say, if you plan to have children, it's best to do that before you start messing with your hormones. And even if you don't want kids, at least go to a sperm bank. If in the future you change your mind, you'll be happy you did. In theory stopping the medication will eventually return your sperm count, but testicular atrophy is a case of better safe than sorry.

Estrone anecdotally helps with breast development, but you have to take really high doses to get enough E2 in your blood orally.
